class Solution {
public String triangleType(int[] nums) {
Arrays.sort(nums);
int x = nums[0];
int y = nums[1];
int z = nums[2];
if (x + y <= z) { // 排序后，只需比较 x+y 和 z
return 'none';
}
if (x == z) { // 排序了，说明 y 也和 x z 相等
return 'equilateral';
}
if (y == z) { // 排序了，说明 y 也和 x z 相等
return 'isosceles';
}
return 'scalene';
}
}

Analysis:

The idea is to find for every 0 the maximum number of 1s it can "cover" and add it to the answer. In this way, we cover all valid substrings starting from 0. 
The left most 1 is added to the answer and we use left - i (i is the index of the previous 1) to add the number of 1s left of it that it can cover.





class Solution {
    public int numberOfSubstrings(String s) {
        char[] cs = s.toCharArray();
        int n = cs.length;
        int[] num = new int[n];
        int i = -1, j = 0;
        for(int k = 0; k < n; k++) {
            if(cs[k] == '1') {
                i = k;
                j = 0;
            }
            else if(cs[k] == '0') {
                if(i != -1) {
                    j = Math.max(j, k - i);
                }
                num[k] = j;
                i++;
            }
        }

        for(int k = 0; k < n - 1; k++) {
            num[k + 1] += num[k];
        }
        return num[n - 1];
    }
}

